        <updateDate>2021-06-24T12:31:35Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Dynamic Glass Act</strong></p> <p>This bill includes electrochromic glass as energy property for purposes of the 30% energy tax credit. The bill defines <i>electrochromic glass</i> as glass that uses electricity to change its light transmittance properties to heat or cool a structure, but only with respect to property whose construction begins before January 1, 2024.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
